 16/12/1955 AIYYAR, T.L. VENKATARAMA AIYYAR, T.L. VENKATARAMA BOSE, VIVIAN 
CITATION: 1956 AIR 213 1955 SCR (2)1066 
ACT:
 Indian Companies Act, 1913 (VII of 1913), s. 153-C sub- clause (3)(a)(i) and s. 162 (v) and (vi)-Application for an order under s.153-C-Validity thereof to be judged on the facts at the time of presentation thereof-Subsequent events- Effect thereof-Order under s. 153-C-Whether competent before facts proved make out a case for winding up under s. 162- Words "just and equitable" in s. 162(vi)-Whether ejusdem generis with the matters mentioned in clauses (i) to (v) of the section-Mere misconduct of Directors in misappropriating funds of a Company-Apart from other circumstances-Whether warrants an order for the winding up of a Company- Circumstances under which an order for winding up can be passed by the court.
 
